@jakirkham - Like I said: I don't know if the issue is with Cython itself or with the package at conda-forge. I don't know how to debug it.

For now, I've opened another one at https://github.com/conda-forge/cython-feedstock/issues/28.
If you don't think it's an issue with your packaging or don't find the second issue helpful, feel free to close it of course.

@astrofrog - This is what I have at the moment for conda list:
https://gist.github.com/cdeil/ea50bed7dc2cf90632d5abdb0bace39b

If you read on you'll see that `conda list` report Cython 0.27 from pip, but then `pip uninstall` tries to remove Cython 0.26 from the conda root env.

@astrofrog - Any chance there is a mix of two Cython installs, also on your machine and our conda install on travis-ci?
